#. type: Title ===
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fine Grain Admin Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sometimes roles like `manage-realm` or `manage-users` are too coarse grain and you want to create\n"
"restricted admin accounts that have more fine grain permissions.  {project_name} allows you to define\n"
"and assign restricted access policies for managing a realm.  Things like:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing one specific client\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing users that belong to a specific group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing membership of a group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Limited user management.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fine grain impersonization control\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Being able to assign a specific restricted set of roles to users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Being able to assign a specific restricted set of roles to a composite role.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Being able to assign a specific restricted set of roles to a client's scope.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "New general policies for viewing and managing users, groups, roles, and clients.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "There's some important things to note about fine grain admin permissions:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fine grain admin permissions were implemented on top of link:{authorizationguide_link}[Authorization Services].  It is highly recommended that you read up on those features before diving into fine grain permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fine grain permissions are only available within <<_per_realm_admin_permissions, dedicated admin consoles>> and admins defined within those realms.  You cannot define cross-realm fine grain permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fine grain permissions are used to grant additional permissions.  You cannot override the\n"
"default behavior of the built in admin roles.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing One Specific Client"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let's look first at allowing\n"
"an admin to manage one client and one client only.  In our example we have a realm\n"
"called `test` and a client called `sales-application`.  In realm `test` we will give a\n"
"user in that realm permission to only manage that application.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot do cross realm fine grain permissions.  Admins in the `master` realm are limited to the predefined admin roles defined in previous chapters.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Permission Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "The first thing we must do is login to the Admin Console so we can set up permissions for that client.  We navigate to the management section\n"
"of the client we want to define fine-grain permissions for.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "You should see a tab menu item called `Permissions`.  Click on that tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:45
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Permissions Tab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client-permissions-tab-off.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "By default, each client is not enabled to do fine grain permissions.  So turn the `Permissions Enabled` switch to on\n"
"to initialize permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you turn the `Permissions Enabled` switch to off, it will delete any and all permissions you have defined for this client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:55
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client-permissions-tab-on.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "When you witch `Permissions Enabled` to on, it initializes various permission objects behind the scenes\n"
"using link:{authorizationguide_link}[Authorization Services].  For this example, we're\n"
"interested in the `manage` permission for the client.  Clicking on that will redirect you\n"
"to the permission that handles the `manage` permission for the client.  All authorization\n"
"objects are contained in the `realm-management` client's `Authorization` tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Manage Permission"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client-manage-permissions.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "When first initialized the `manage` permission does not have any policies associated with it.\n"
"You will need to create one by going to the policy tab.  To get there fast, click on\n"
"the `Authorization` link shown in the above image. Then click on the policies tab.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "There's a pull down menu on this page called `Create policy`.  There's a multitude of policies\n"
"you can define.  You can define a policy that is associated with a role or a group or even define\n"
"rules in Javascript.  For this simple example, we're going to create a `User Policy`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "User Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client-user-policy.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "This policy will match a hard-coded user in the user database.  In this case it is the `sales-admin` user.  We must then go back to the\n"
"`sales-application` client's `manage` permission page and assign the policy to the permission object.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assign User Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-client-assign-user-policy.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `sales-admin` user can now has permission to manage the `sales-application` client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "There's one more thing we have to do.  Go to the `Role Mappings` tab and assign the `query-clients`\n"
"role to the `sales-admin`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assign query-clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-assign-query-clients.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "Why do you have to do this?  This role tells the Admin Console\n"
"what menu items to render when the `sales-admin` visits the Admin Console.  The `query-clients`\n"
"role tells the Admin Console that it should render client menus for the `sales-admin` user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "IMPORTANT If you do not set the `query-clients` role, restricted admins like `sales-admin` will not see any menu options when they log into the Admin Console\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:97
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing It Out."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:101
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next we log out of the master realm and and re-login to the <<_per_realm_admin_permissions, dedicated admin console>> for the `test` realm\n"
"using the `sales-admin` as a username.  This is located under `/auth/admin/test/console`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sales Admin Login"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-sales-admin-login.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "This admin is now able to manage this one client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Restrict User Role Mapping"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "Another thing you might want to do is to restrict the set a roles an admin is allowed\n"
"to assign to a user.  Continuing our last example, let's expand the permission set of the 'sales-admin'\n"
"user so that he can also control which users are allowed to access this application.  Through fine grain permissions we can\n"
"enable it so that the `sales-admin` can only assign roles that grant specific access to\n"
"the `sales-application`.  We can also restrict it so that the admin can only map roles\n"
"and not perform any other types of user administration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `sales-application` has defined three different client roles.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sales Application Roles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-sales-application-roles.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:124
#, no-wrap
msgid "We want the `sales-admin` user to be able to map these roles to any user in the system.  The\n"
"first step to do this is to allow the role to be mapped by the admin.  If we click on the\n"
"`viewLeads` role, you'll see that there is a `Permissions` tab for this role.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "View Leads Role Permission Tab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:127
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-view-leads-role-tab.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "If we click on that tab and turn the `Permissions Enabled` on, you'll see that there\n"
"are a number of actions we can apply policies to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "View Leads Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-view-leads-permissions.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "The one we are interested in is `map-role`.  Click on this permission and add the same\n"
"User Policy that was created in the earlier example.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "Map-roles Permission"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-map-roles-permission.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "What we've done is say that the `sales-admin` can map the `viewLeads` role.  What we have\n"
"not done is specify which users the admin is allowed to map this role too.  To do that\n"
"we must go to the `Users` section of the admin console for this realm.  Clicking on the\n"
"`Users` left menu item brings us to the users interface of the realm.  You should see a\n"
"`Permissions` tab.  Click on that and enable it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "Users Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-users-permissions.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "The permission we are interested in is `map-roles`.  This is a restrictive policy\n"
"in that it only allows admins the ability to map roles to a user.  If we click on the\n"
"`map-roles` permission and again add the User Policy we created for this, our `sales-admin`\n"
"will be able to map roles to any user.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "The last thing we have to do is add the `view-users` role to the `sales-admin`.  This will\n"
"allow the admin to view users in the realm he wants to add the `sales-application` roles to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add view-users"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-add-view-users.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "You will see that now the `sales-admin` can view users in the system.  If you select one of the\n"
"users you'll see that each user detail page is read only, except for the `Role Mappings` tab.\n"
"Going to these tab you'll find that there are no `Available` roles for the admin to\n"
"map to the user except when we browse the `sales-application` roles.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:171
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add viewLeads"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:173
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/fine-grain-add-view-leads.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "We've only specified that the `sales-admin` can map the `viewLeads` role.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "Per Client map-roles Shortcut"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "It would be tedious if we had to do this for every client role that the `sales-application` published.\n"
"to make things easier, there's a way to specify that an admin can map any role defined\n"
"by a client.  If we log back into the admin console to our master realm admin and go back\n"
"  to the `sales-application` permissions page, you'll see the `map-roles` permission.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client map-roles Permission"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you grant access to this particular parmission to an admin, that admin will be able\n"
"map any role defined by the client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "Full List of Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can do a lot more with fine grain permissions beyond managing a specific client or the specific roles of a client.\n"
"This chapter defines the whole list of permission types that can be described for\n"
"a realm.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "Role"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "When going to the `Permissions` tab for a specific role, you will see these\n"
"permission types listed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:200
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-role"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can map this role to a user.  These policies\n"
"only specify that the role can be mapped to a user, not that the admin is allowed\n"
"to perform user role mapping tasks.  The admin will also have to have manage or\n"
"role mapping permissions.  See <<_users-permissions, Users Permissions>> for more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-role-composite"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can map this role as a composite to another role.\n"
"An admin can define roles for a client if he has manage permissions for that client\n"
"but he will not be able to add composites to those roles unless he has the\n"
"`map-role-composite` privileges for the role he wants to add as a composite.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-role-client-scope"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can apply this role to the scope of a client.\n"
"Even if the admin can manage the client, he will not have permission to\n"
"create tokens for that client that contain this role unless this privilege\n"
"is granted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:216
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:220
#, no-wrap
msgid "When going to the `Permissions` tab for a specific client, you will see these\n"
"permission types listed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:221
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:255
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "view"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:223
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can view the client's configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:223
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:257
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "manage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can view and manage the client's configuration.\n"
"There is some issues with this in that privileges could be leaked unintentionally.\n"
"For example, the admin could define a protocol mapper that hardcoded a role\n"
"even if the admin does not have privileges to map the role to the client's scope.\n"
"This is currently the limitation of protocol mappers as they don't have a way\n"
"to assign individual permissions to them like roles do.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "configure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reduced set of prileges to manage the client.  Its like the `manage` scope except\n"
"the admin is not allowed to define protocol mappers, change the client template,\n"
"or the client's scope.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:234
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:262
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-roles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can map any role defined by the client to a user.\n"
"This is a shortcut, easy-of-use feature to avoid having to defin policies\n"
"for each and every role defined by the client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-roles-composite"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can map any role defined by the client\n"
"as a composite to another role.\n"
"This is a shortcut, easy-of-use feature to avoid having to define policies\n"
"for each and every role defined by the client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "map-roles-client-scope"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:248
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can map any role defined by the client\n"
"to the scope of another client.\n"
"This is a shortcut, easy-of-use feature to avoid having to define policies\n"
"for each and every role defined by the client.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:254
#, no-wrap
msgid "When going to the `Permissions` tab for all users, you will see these\n"
"permission types listed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:257
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can view all users in the realm.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:262
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can manage all users in the realm.  This\n"
"permission grants the admin the privilege to perfor user role mappings, but\n"
"it does not specify which roles the admin is allowed to map.  You'll need to\n"
"define the privilege for each role you want the admin to be able to map.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is a subset of the privileges granted by the `manage` scope.  In this\n"
"case the admin is only allowed to map roles.  The admin is not allowed to perform\n"
"any other user management operation.  Also, like `manage`, the roles that the\n"
"admin is allowed to apply must be specified per role or per set of roles if dealing\n"
"with client roles.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "manage-group-membership"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "Similar to `map-roles` except that it pertains to group membership: which\n"
"groups a user can be added or removed from.  These\n"
"policies just grant the admin permission to manage group membership, not which\n"
"groups the admin is allowed to manage membership for.  You'll have to\n"
"specify policies for each group's `manage-members` permission.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "impersonate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if the admin is allowed to impersonate other users.  These\n"
"policies are applied to the admin's attributes and role mappings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "user-impersonated"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide which users can be impersonated.  These policies will be\n"
"applied to the user being impersonated.  For example, you might want to define\n"
"a policy that will forbid anybody from impersonating a user that has admin\n"
"privileges.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:287
#, no-wrap
msgid "When going to the `Permissions` tab for a specific group, you will see these\n"
"permission types listed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if the admin can view information about the group.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if the admin can manage the configuration of the group.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "view-members"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:294
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if the admin can view the user details of members of the group.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:294
#, no-wrap
msgid "manage-members"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if the admin can manage the users that belong to this group.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "manage-membership"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/admin-console-permissions/fine-grain.adoc:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "Policies that decide if an admin can change the membership of the group.  Add or\n"
"remove members from the group.\n"
msgstr ""

